{"repo": "quantumlib/OpenFermion", "pull_number": 1280, "instance_id": "quantumlib__OpenFermion-1280", "issue_numbers": [1268], "base_commit": "a311619dc6a60aafec0c28b82019eee5b907a70c", "patch": "diff --git a/check/mypy b/check/mypy\nindex f68acd866..c9c72ac9c 100755\n--- a/check/mypy\n+++ b/check/mypy\n@@ -14,7 +14,7 @@\n # limitations under the License.\n \n ################################################################################\n-# Runs mypy on the repository using a preconfigured mypy.ini file.\n+# Runs mypy on the repository starting from the root.\n #\n # Usage:\n #     check/mypy [--flags]\n@@ -25,7 +25,7 @@ cd \"$( cd \"$( dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\" )\" && pwd )\" || exit 1\n cd \"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)\" || exit 1\n \n echo -e -n \"\\033[31m\"\n-mypy --config-file=dev_tools/conf/mypy.ini \"$@\" .\n+mypy \"$@\" .\n result=$?\n echo -e -n \"\\033[0m\"\n \ndiff --git a/dev_tools/conf/mypy.ini b/dev_tools/conf/mypy.ini\ndeleted file mode 100644\nindex bd000aebc..000000000\n--- a/dev_tools/conf/mypy.ini\n+++ /dev/null\n@@ -1,39 +0,0 @@\n-# Copyright 2025 Google LLC\n-#\n-# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n-# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n-# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n-#\n-#     https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n-#\n-# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n-# distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n-# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n-# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n-# limitations under the License.\n-\n-[mypy]\n-implicit_optional = True\n-\n-# TODO: this is temporary for 1.7.0 release. Remove this & fix the errors.\n-ignore_errors = True\n-\n-[mypy-__main__]\n-follow_imports = silent\n-ignore_missing_imports = True\n-\n-# 3rd-party libs for which we don't have stubs\n-[mypy-apiclient.*,numpy.*,pytest.*,scipy.*,,_pytest.*,h5py,pyscf.*,pubchempy,pybtas,absl,tensorflow_docs]\n-follow_imports = silent\n-ignore_missing_imports = True\n-\n-# Adding \"sympy.* or mypy-sympy to the above list (3rd-party libs for which we\n-# don't have stubs) doesn't ignore \"cannot find module 'sympy' error\n-[mypy-sympy.*]\n-ignore_missing_imports = True\n-\n-[mypy-tensorflow_docs.*]\n-ignore_missing_imports = True\n-\n-[mypy-deprecation]\n-follow_untyped_imports = True\ndiff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml\nindex 30bff2879..6e7d7b7b2 100644\n--- a/pyproject.toml\n+++ b/pyproject.toml\n@@ -22,3 +22,43 @@ skip-magic-trailing-comma = true\n # Speed up pytest-cov on Python 3.12+ by enabling sys.monitoring if possible.\n core = \"sysmon\"\n disable_warnings = [\"no-sysmon\"]\n+\n+[tool.mypy]\n+implicit_optional = true\n+\n+# TODO: this is temporary for 1.7.0 release. Remove this & fix the errors.\n+ignore_errors = true\n+\n+[[tool.mypy.overrides]]\n+module = \"__main__\"\n+follow_imports = \"silent\"\n+ignore_missing_imports = true\n+\n+[[tool.mypy.overrides]]\n+module = [\n+    \"_pytest.*\",\n+    \"absl\",\n+    \"apiclient.*\",\n+    \"h5py\",\n+    \"numpy.*\",\n+    \"pubchempy\",\n+    \"pybtas\",\n+    \"pyscf.*\",\n+    \"pytest.*\",\n+    \"scipy.*\",\n+    \"tensorflow_docs\",\n+]\n+follow_imports = \"silent\"\n+ignore_missing_imports = true\n+\n+[[tool.mypy.overrides]]\n+module = \"sympy.*\"\n+ignore_missing_imports = true\n+\n+[[tool.mypy.overrides]]\n+module = \"tensorflow_docs.*\"\n+ignore_missing_imports = true\n+\n+[[tool.mypy.overrides]]\n+module = \"deprecation\"\n+follow_untyped_imports = true\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Move tool configuration settings into `pyproject.toml`\n### Is your feature request related to a use case or problem?\n\nOpenFermion currently puts the configuration files for some tools like pylint into `dev_tools/conf/`. This location is unexpected for most modern developers, who probably expect to find the config files at the top level of the repo.\n\n### What solution or approach do you envision?\n\n We should follow the more modern approach of putting such configurations in the top-level `pyproject.toml` file.\n\n### How urgent is this for you?\n\nNone\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/quantumlib/OpenFermion/commit/c99faf4a01583ca50a02815d669c771ee7fc9b7f", "https://github.com/quantumlib/OpenFermion/commit/e5bce5efa029d0f9a97c0cd8cb6efa97882c62f2", "https://github.com/quantumlib/OpenFermion/commit/b0beb257db21794ab5e3c6b5601884e843eb3b57", "https://github.com/quantumlib/OpenFermion/commit/731767b9e49cbe01c7bb253e4eeb9f4b4c62fc5f", "https://github.com/quantumlib/OpenFermion/commit/99d4fe7f1df99070e4027a33c05dc38292512890", "https://github.com/quantumlib/OpenFermion/commit/e544494c68a24cd3fbdbc927b26cadee3b1efec6", "https://github.com/quantumlib/OpenFermion/commit/e2f57b43995120793c6774b731da1cd6c6b3af3f"], "created_at": "2026-04-23T20:24:14Z"}
